main event: A report detailing observations of unidentified flying objects was submitted, including a sighting in Hugo, Oklahoma on February 9, 1965.
interesting points: Object was described as disk-shaped and shiny, The object moved erratically and very fast from North to South, 14 objects were reported in a different sighting on February 16, 1965, These objects were detected both visually and on radar, The sighting lasted about 5 minutes, 15 seconds with impressive formation.
sighted object: disk-shaped shiny object and 14 bright shiny objects
